  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this clinical trial is to demonstrate that MelaFind®, a new instrument that
      uses machine vision for non-invasive early detection of cutaneous pigmented malignant
      melanoma, is safe and effective. MelaFind® acquires digital images of the lesion with
      illumination in different spectral bands, from visible to near infrared, and automatically
      analyzes these images. Diagnostic accuracy of MelaFind® and that of study dermatologists will
      be evaluated. The reference standard will be final interpretation of lesions by central
      dermatohistopathology.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
